template.name: Service Zabbix Server
template.description:
Base Zabbix server monitoring template.
Version: 1.0.4 (2018-06-11) URL: https://github.com/kloczek/zabbix-templates/tree/master/Service%20Zabbix%20Server
Notes: * Host with this template must be monitored without any proxy.

item.description: Number of monitored hosts.
Number of enabled items (supported and not supported).

item.name: items::unsupported
item.description: Number of not supported items.

item.name: queue::preprocessing
item.description: Count of values enqueued in the preprocessing queue.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "alerter" processes are busy during the last minute. "alerter" processes are responsible for sending alarms notifications.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "alert manager" process is busy during the last minute. "alert manager" process is managing alerts pool queue.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "configuration syncer" process is busy during the last minute. "configuration syncer" process is for managing in-memory cache of configuration data.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "discoverer" process is busy during the last minute. "discoverer" process is responsible for discovery of the hosts.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "escalator" process is busy during the last minute. "escalator" process is responsible for escalation of actions.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "history syncer" processes are busy during the last minute. "history syncer" processes are responsible for history data writing to DB backend.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time "housekeeper" process which is responsible for removal of old historical data. This metrics should have only two values 0 and 100% because it is only one housekeeper process. When it is 100% it means that housekeeper is active.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "http poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "http poller" processes are responsible for web monitoring polling.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "icmp pinger" processes are busy during the last minute. "icmp pinger" processes are responsible for polling icmpping checks..

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "ipmi manager" process is busy during the last minute. "ipmi manager" process is responsible for IPMI poller management.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "ipmi poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "ipmi poller" processes are responsible for poller for IPMI checks.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "java poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "java poller" processes are responsible for polling Java checks.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "poller" processes are responsible for polling for passive checks, calculate values of calculated items and zabbix server internal checks.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "preprocessing manager" process is busy during the last minute. "preprocessing manager" process is responsible for managing of preprocessing tasks.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "preprocessing worker" processes are busy during the last minute. "preprocessing worker" processes are responsible for processing of all items preprocess rules.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "proxy poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "proxy poller" processes are responsible for polling for passive proxies.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "self-monitoring" process is busy during the last minute. "self-monitoring" process is responsible for collecting internal server statistics.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "snmp trapper" process is busy during the last minute. "snmp trapper" process is for receiving SNMP traps.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "task manager" process is busy during the last minute. "task manager" process is responsible for manually closing problems.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "timer" process is busy during the last minute. "timer" process is responsible for evaluation of time-related trigger functions and maintenances.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "trapper" processes are busy during the last minute. "trapper" processes are responsible for receive data from active check items.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "unreachable poller" processes are busy during the last minute. "unreachable poller" processes are responsible for polling unreachable hosts.

item.name: proc::$4::$2 %
item.description: Average percent of the time of the "vmware collector" processes are busy during the last minute. "vmware collector" processes are responsible for data gathering from VMware servers.

item.name: queue::$2
item.description: Number of monitored items in the Queue which are delayed by 1 minute or more.

item.name: queue::$2
item.description: Number of monitored items in the Queue which are delayed by 5 minutes or more.

item.name: queue::$2
item.description: Number of monitored items in the Queue which are delayed by 10 min or more.

item.name: queue::$2
item.description: Number of monitored items in the Queue which are delayed by 10s or more.

item.name: queue::$2
item.description: Number of monitored items in the Queue which are delayed by 30s or more.
Size of Zabbix server configuration cache buffer free memory.
Percent of Zabbix server configuration cache buffer free memory.
Size of Zabbix server configuration cache buffer used memory.

item.name: items::nvps
item.description: Required performance of the Zabbix server in new values per second expected.
Number of enabled triggers in Zabbix database, with all items enabled on enabled hosts.
Uptime of te Zabbix server process in seconds.
Percent of Zabbix server value cache free buffer.
Zabbix server number of cache hits (history values taken from the cache).
Zabbix server values cache misses (history values taken from the database).
Zabbix server values cache total number of requests.
Size of free history cache. A low number indicates performance problems on the database side.
History cache feree used to store item values. A low number indicates performance problems on the database side.
Total size of free history cache.
The size of the history cache to store item values. A high number indicates performance problems on the database side.
Size of free trends cache. A low number indicates performance problems on the database side.
Percent of the tends cache free space. A low number indicates performance problems on the database side.
Total size of the trends cache.
Size of used trends cache. A high number indicates performance problems on the database side.
Total number of values per second processed by Zabbix server except unsupported items.
Total number of values per second processed by Zabbix server except unsupported items.
Number of log values per second processed by Zabbix server.
Number of all item per second which processing resulted in item becoming unsupported or keeping that state by Zabbix server.
Number of character/string values per second processed by Zabbix server.
Number of text values per second processed by Zabbix server.
Number of unsigned integer values per second processed by Zabbix server.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::CacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (< 5%)
trigger.description: Consider increasing CacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/CacheSize file.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::CacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (< 15%)
trigger.description: Consider increasing CacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/CacheSize file.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::CacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (> 80%)
trigger.description: Consider decrease CacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/CacheSize file.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::HistoryCacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (< 5%)
trigger.description: Consider increasing HistoryCacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/HistoryCacheSize file.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::HistoryCacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (< 15%)
trigger.description: Consider increasing HistoryCacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/HistoryCacheSize file.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_server::HistoryCacheSize {ITEM.VALUE} free (> 80%)
trigger.description: Consider decrease HistoryCacheSize in the /etc/zabbix/zabbix_server/HistoryCacheSize file.
